ell\u00f3n.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eldiario.es/cv/Gobierno-prohibe-multitudinarios-Fallas-coronavirus_0_1004400103.html|title=El Gobierno valenciano aplaza las Fallas de Val\u00e8ncia y la Magdalena de Castell\u00f3n por el coronavirus|website=eldiario.es|language=es|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n;11 March\n* The Catalan government followed the steps of the Spanish government taken the previous day and suspended events with more than one thousand attendees in the region.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eldiario.es/catalunya/Catalunya-prohibe-eventos-personas-coronavirus_0_1004749678.html|title=Catalunya proh\u00edbe los eventos de m\u00e1s de 1.000 personas por la crisis del coronavirus|last=Rodr\u00edguez|first=Pau|website=eldiario.es|language=es|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Madrid cancelled the main tribute in honour of the [[2004 Madrid train bombings|11-M terrorist attacks]] in Atocha.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ultimahora.es/noticias/nacional/2020/03/11/1147631/madrid-coronavirus-condiciona-aniversario-del-11m.html|title=Un 11M m\u00e1s, pero no uno cualquiera|date=11 March 2020|website=\u00daltima Hora|language=es|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n* First death reported in Extremadura.<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=Junta_Ex|number=1237685241218768897|title=@GFVara: En Extremadura hay dos casos positivos m\u00e1s, uno de ellos lamentablemente ha fallecido. Nuestra solidaridad y condolencias a la familia #Covid19 #Coronaviruspic.twitter.com/TQksGf1OT2|author=Junta de Extremadura|date=11 March 2020|language=es|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n* A second national deputy of the far-right Vox that did not have any contact with the first one tests positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/politica/20200311/474089319939/segundo-positivo-coronavirus-vox.html|title=Un segundo diputado de Vox da positivo en coronavirus|date=11 March 2020|website=La Vanguardia|language=es|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n* The [[Assembly