ar=2012|isbn=9781442218369|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lTaFL7EwkikC}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin|35em}}\n\n===Secondary sources===\n* {{cite journal|last=Binder|first=Frederick Moore|title=James Buchanan: Jacksonian Expansionist|journal=Historian|date=1992|volume=55|issue=1|pages=69\u201384|issn=0018-2370|doi=10.1111/j.1540-6563.1992.tb00886.x}}\n* {{cite book|last=Binder|first=Frederick Moore|title=James Buchanan and the American Empire |date=1994 |publisher=Susquehanna University Press|isbn=9780945636649}}\n* {{cite book|editor-last=Birkner|editor-first=Michael J.|title=James Buchanan and the Political Crisis of the 1850s|date=1996|publisher=Susquehanna University Press|isbn=9780945636892}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Meerse|first=David|title=Buchanan, the Patronage, and the Lecompton Constitution: a Case Study|journal=Civil War History|date=1995|volume=41|issue=4|pages=291\u2013312|issn=0009-8078|doi=10.1353/cwh.1995.0017}}\n* [[Allan Nevins|Nevins, Allan]]. ''The Emergence of Lincoln'' 2 vols. (1960) highly detailed narrative of his presidency\n* Nichols, Roy Franklin; ''The Democratic Machine, 1850\u20131854'' (1923), [https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=1112776 detailed narrative; online]\n* {{cite book|editor1-last=Quist|editor1-first=John W.|editor2-last=Birkner|editor2-first=Michael J.|title=James Buchanan and the Coming of the Civil War|date=2013|publisher=University Press of Florida|isbn=9780813044262}}\n* {{cite book|last=Rhodes|first=James Ford|title=History of the United States from the Compromise of 1850 to the End of the Roosevelt Administration|volume=2|year=1906|publisher=Macmillan|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5G9KAAAAYAAJ}}\n* {{cite book|author-link=Joel H. Silbey|last=Silbey|first=Joel H.|title=A Companion to the Antebellum Presidents 1837\u20131861|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mgCJAgAAQBAJ|year=2014|publisher=Wiley|pages=397\u2013464|isbn=9781118609293}}\n* {{cite book|last=Updike|first=John|title=Buchanan Dying: A Play|date=2013|orig-year=1974|publisher=Random House Publishing Group|isbn=9780812984910}}\n\n===Primary sources===\n* Buchanan, James. ''[http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/?pid=29501 Fourth Annual Message to Congress.]'' (1860, December 3).\n* Buchanan, James. ''[http://deila.dickinson.edu/theirownwords/title/0010.htm Mr Buchanan's Administration on the Eve of the Rebellion]'' (1866)\n* ''National Intelligencer'' (1859)\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikisource author}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons}}\n* [https://www.whitehouse.gov/1600/presidents/jamesbuchanan White House biography]\n* {{CongBio|B001005}}\n* [https://www.loc.gov/rr/program/bib/presidents/buchanan/index.html James Buchanan: A Resource Guide] from the Library of Congress\n* The [http://www2.hsp.org/collections/manuscripts/b/Buchanan0091.html James Buchanan papers], spanning the entirety of his legal, political and diplomatic career, are available for research use at the [[Historical Society of Pennsylvania]].\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080726185412/http://www.americanpresident.org/history/jamesbuchanan/ University of Virginia article: Buchanan biography]\n* [http://www.wheatland.org/ Wheatland]\n* [http://www.tulane.edu/~sumter/Buchanan.html James Buchanan] at [[Tulane University]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070501064751/http://www.millercenter.virginia.edu/index.php/academic/americanpresident/buchanan Essay on James Buchanan and shorter essays on each member of his cabinet and First Lady] from the [[Miller Center of Public Affairs]]\n* [https://www.dcnr.pa.gov/StateParks/FindAPark/BuchanansBirthplaceStatePark/Pages/default.aspx Buchanan's Birthplace State Park, Franklin County, Pennsylvania]\n* [http://www.c-span.org/video/?125214-1/life-portrait-james-buchanan \"Life Portrait of James Buchanan\"], from [[C-SPAN]]'s ''[[American Presidents: Life Portraits]]'', June 21, 1999\n\n'''Primary sources'''\n* {{Gutenberg author |id=1648}}\n* {{Librivox author |id=11288}}\n* {