re=[[William Wilkins (U.S. politician)|William Wilkins]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of United States Senators from Pennsylvania|United States Senator (Class 3) from Pennsylvania]]|years=1834\u20131845|alongside=[[Samuel McKean]], [[Daniel Sturgeon]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Simon Cameron]]}}\n\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[John C. Calhoun]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States Secretary of State]]|years=1845\u20131849}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[John M. Clayton]]}}\n\n{{s-bef|before=[[Franklin Pierce]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[President of the United States]]|years=1857\u20131861}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Abraham Lincoln]]}}\n\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Franklin Pierce]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] [[List of United States Democratic Party presidential tickets|nominee]] for President of the United States|years=[[1856 United States presidential election|1856]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Stephen A. Douglas]]\u00b9|after2=[[John C. Breckinridge]]}}\n\n{{s-hon}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Martin Van Buren]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Oldest living President of the United States]]|years=1862\u20131868}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Millard Fillmore]]}}\n{{s-ref|The Democratic Party split in [[1860 United States presidential election|1860]], producing two presidential candidates. Douglas was nominated by Northern Democrats; Breckinridge was nominated by Southern Democrats.}}\n}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Articles related to James Buchanan\n|list1=\n{{US Presidents}}\n{{USDemPresNominees}}\n{{USSecState}}\n{{USSenPA}}\n{{Polk cabinet}}\n{{Buchanan cabinet}}\n{{US Ambassadors to the UK}}\n{{US Ambassadors to Russia}}\n{{SenForeignRelationsCommitteeChairmen}}\n{{US House Judiciary chairs}}\n{{1844 United States presidential election}}\n{{1848 United States presidential election}}\n{{1852 United States presidential election}}\n{{1856 United States presidential election}}\n}}\n{{Portal bar|Biography|American Civil War|United States|Politics|Latter-day Saints|Pennsylvania|Law}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSOR